{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775840295827,"sessionID":"ses_287abc318ffel7tpmE2F2RUOxc","part":{"id":"prt_d78547b62001UEe9OwZlFtwwaT","messageID":"msg_d785471f4001q8hEdjY1dI4ODc","sessionID":"ses_287abc318ffel7tpmE2F2RUOxc","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-c3066f8183894a3cbf37cd23b0afbfa9","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/deployment/tasks.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/deployment/tasks.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-001 Task Checklist: CRD AgentRuntime 类型定义\n2: \n3: ## Status\n4: Stage: ST-3 (Design) - Completed  \n5: Phase: ST-4 (Implementation) - In Progress\n6: \n7: ---\n8: \n9: ## Phase 1: Type Definition\n10: ### [ ] TASK-001: Create package directory structure\n11: **Description**: Create `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/` directory structure for CRD type definitions.\n12: \n13: **Verification**:\n14: ```bash\n15: test -d pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1 && echo \"Directory exists\" || echo \"Directory missing\"\n16: ```\n17: \n18: **Acceptance Criteria**:\n19: - Directory `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/` exists\n20: - Directory is writable and follows Go package conventions\n21: \n22: ---\n23: \n24: ### [ ] TASK-002: Define TargetPort helper type\n25: **Description**: Create `TargetPort` struct with port, protocol, name, and pathPrefix fields.\n26: \n27: **Implementation File**: `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime_types.go`\n28: \n29: **Requirements**:\n30: - `Port int32` - required field with validation markers for 1-65535 range\n31: - `Protocol string` - required enum validation for \"HTTP\"|\"HTTPS\"\n32: - `Name string` - optional field\n33: - `PathPrefix string` - optional field\n34: - JSON tags use camelCase\n35: \n36: **Verification**:\n37: ```bash\n38: go test ./pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/ -run TestTargetPort\n39: ```\n40: \n41: **Acceptance Criteria**:\n42: - `TargetPort` struct compiles without errors\n43: - `Port` field has `+kubebuilder:validation:Minimum=1` and `+kubebuilder:validation:Maximum=65535` markers\n44: - `Protocol` field has `+kubebuilder:validation:Enum=HTTP;HTTPS` marker\n45: - JSON tags are correctly formatted\n46: \n47: ---\n48: \n49: ### [ ] TASK-003: Define PodTemplateSpec helper type\n50: **Description**: Create `PodTemplateSpec` struct with metadata and spec fields.\n51: \n52: **Implementation File**: `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime_types.go`\n53: \n54: **Requirements**:\n55: - `Metadata metav1.ObjectMeta` - optional field\n56: - `Spec PodSpec` - optional field\n57: - Reuses Kubernetes core v1 types\n58: \n59: **Verification**:\n60: ```bash\n61: go test ./pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/ -run TestPodTemplateSpec\n62: ```\n63: \n64: **Acceptance Criteria**:\n65: - `PodTemplateSpec` struct compiles without errors\n66: - Fields reference Kubernetes core v1 types correctly\n67: - JSON tags use camelCase\n68: \n69: ---\n70: \n71: ### [ ] TASK-004: Define AgentRuntimeSpec\n72: **Description**: Create `AgentRuntimeSpec` struct with all required fields and default values.\n73: \n74: **Implementation File**: `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime_types.go`\n75: \n76: **Requirements**:\n77: - `MaxSessionDuration string` - default \"8h\"\n78: - `SessionTimeout string` - default \"15m\"\n79: - `TargetPort []TargetPort` - minimum 1 item required\n80: - `PodTemplate PodTemplateSpec` - required field\n81: - Default value markers: `+kubebuilder:default=\"8h\"` and `+kubebuilder:default=\"15m\"`\n82: \n83: **Verification**:\n84: ```bash\n85: go test ./pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/ -run TestAgentRuntimeSpec\n86: ```\n87: \n88: **Acceptance Criteria**:\n89: - `AgentRuntimeSpec` struct compiles without errors\n90: - Default value markers are correctly applied\n91: - Required fields are properly tagged\n92: - `TargetPort` has `+kubebuilder:validation:MinItems=1` marker\n93: \n94: ---\n95: \n96: ### [ ] TASK-005: Define AgentRuntimeStatus\n97: **Description**: Create `AgentRuntimeStatus` struct with conditions and observed generation.\n98: \n99: **Implementation File**: `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime_types.go`\n100: \n101: **Requirements**:\n102: - `Conditions []metav1.Condition` - optional field\n103: - `ObservedGeneration int64` - optional field\n104: - Follows Kubernetes status conventions\n105: \n106: **Verification**:\n107: ```bash\n108: go test ./pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/ -run TestAgentRuntimeStatus\n109: ```\n110: \n111: **Acceptance Criteria**:\n112: - `AgentRuntimeStatus` struct compiles without errors\n113: - `Conditions` field uses standard Kubernetes `metav1.Condition` type\n114: - JSON tags use camelCase with `omitempty` for optional fields\n115: \n116: ---\n117: \n118: ### [ ] TASK-006: Define AgentRuntime main type\n119: **Description**: Create `AgentRuntime` struct with TypeMeta, ObjectMeta, Spec, and Status.\n120: \n121: **Implementation File**: `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime_types.go`\n122: \n123: **Requirements**:\n124: - Embeds `metav1.TypeMeta` and `metav1.ObjectMeta`\n125: - Contains `Spec AgentRuntimeSpec` and `Status AgentRuntimeStatus`\n126: - Kubebuilder markers:\n127:   - `+kubebuilder:object:root=true`\n128:   - `+kubebuilder:subresource:status`\n129:   - `+kubebuilder:resource:shortName=art`\n130:   - `+kubebuilder:printcolumn:name=\"Age\",type=\"date\",JSONPath=\".metadata.creationTimestamp\"`\n131: \n132: **Verification**:\n133: ```bash\n134: go test ./pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/ -run TestAgentRuntime\n135: ```\n136: \n137: **Acceptance Criteria**:\n138: - `AgentRuntime` struct compiles without errors\n139: - All kubebuilder markers are present and correct\n140: - ShortName \"art\" is configured\n141: - Print column for Age is configured\n142: \n143: ---\n144: \n145: ### [ ] TASK-007: Define AgentRuntimeList type\n146: **Description**: Create `AgentRuntimeList` struct for collection operations.\n147: \n148: **Implementation File**: `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime_types.go`\n149: \n150: **Requirements**:\n151: - Embeds `metav1.TypeMeta` and `metav1.ListMeta`\n152: - Contains `Items []AgentRuntime`\n153: - Has `+kubebuilder:object:root=true` marker\n154: \n155: **Verification**:\n156: ```bash\n157: go test ./pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/ -run TestAgentRuntimeList\n158: ```\n159: \n160: **Acceptance Criteria**:\n161: - `AgentRuntimeList` struct compiles without errors\n162: - `Items` field is properly typed as `[]AgentRuntime`\n163: - Kubebuilder root object marker is present\n164: \n165: ---\n166: \n167: ### [ ] TASK-008: Create doc.go package documentation\n168: **Description**: Create `doc.go` with package-level markers for code generation.\n169: \n170: **Implementation File**: `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/doc.go`\n171: \n172: **Requirements**:\n173: - Package comment describing the v1alpha1 runtime API\n174: - `+k8s:deepcopy-gen=package` marker\n175: - `+groupName=runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` marker\n176: \n177: **Verification**:\n178: ```bash\n179: grep -q \"k8s:deepcopy-gen=package\" pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/doc.go\n180: grep -q \"groupName=runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\" pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/doc.go\n181: ```\n182: \n183: **Acceptance Criteria**:\n184: - `doc.go` file exists\n185: - Contains required code generation markers\n186: - Package comment is present\n187: \n188: ---\n189: \n190: ## Phase 2: Scheme Registration\n191: ### [ ] TASK-009: Create groupversion_info.go\n192: **Description**: Create `groupversion_info.go` with GroupVersion constants and SchemeBuilder.\n193: \n194: **Implementation File**: `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/groupversion_info.go`\n195: \n196: **Requirements**:\n197: - Define `GroupVersion = schema.GroupVersion{Group: \"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\", Version: \"v1alpha1\"}`\n198: - Create `SchemeBuilder` using `scheme.Builder`\n199: - Export `AddToScheme` function\n200: - Export `Resource(resource string)` function\n201: - Has `+groupName=runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` marker\n202: \n203: **Verification**:\n204: ```bash\n205: go test ./pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/ -run TestGroupVersionInfo\n206: ```\n207: \n208: **Acceptance Criteria**:\n209: - `GroupVersion` constant is correctly defined\n210: - `SchemeBuilder` and `AddToScheme` are exported\n211: - `Resource()` function returns correct `GroupResource`\n212: - Code compiles without errors\n213: \n214: ---\n215: \n216: ### [ ] TASK-010: Create register.go for scheme registration\n217: **Description**: Create `register.go` with kind/resource conversion functions and scheme setup.\n218: \n219: **Implementation File**: `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/register.go`\n220: \n221: **Requirements**:\n222: - Define `SchemeGroupVersion` constant\n223: - Export `Kind(kind string)` function\n224: - Export `Resource(resource string)` function\n225: - Initialize `SchemeBuilder` and `localSchemeBuilder`\n226: - Export `AddToScheme` function\n227: - Register metav1 types in `init()` function\n228: \n229: **Verification**:\n230: ```bash\n231: go test ./pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/ -run TestRegister\n232: ```\n233: \n234: **Acceptance Criteria**:\n235: - `SchemeGroupVersion` matches groupversion_info.go\n236: - `Kind()` and `Resource()` functions work correctly\n237: - `AddToScheme` function is exported and functional\n238: - metav1 types are registered in init()\n239: \n240: ---\n241: \n242: ### [ ] TASK-011: Register AgentRuntime types in scheme\n243: **Description**: Ensure `AgentRuntime` and `AgentRuntimeList` are registered in the scheme.\n244: \n245: **Implementation**: Modify `register.go` or create registration function\n246: \n247: **Requirements**:\n248: - Register `AgentRuntime` with correct `GroupVersionKind`\n249: - Register `AgentRuntimeList` with correct `GroupVersionKind`\n250: - Enable `DeepCopy` code generation\n251: \n252: **Verification**:\n253: ```bash\n254: go test ./pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/ -run TestTypeRegistration\n255: ```\n256: \n257: **Acceptance Criteria**:\n258: - Types are registered in scheme\n259: - `runtime.Object` interface is implemented\n260: - `DeepCopy` methods will be generated\n261: \n262: ---\n263: \n264: ## Phase 3: Code Generation\n265: ### [ ] TASK-012: Generate DeepCopy methods\n266: **Description**: Run controller-gen to generate `zz_generated.deepcopy.go`.\n267: \n268: **Command**:\n269: ```bash\n270: controller-gen object paths=\"./pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/...\"\n271: ```\n272: \n273: **Verification**:\n274: ```bash\n275: test -f pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/zz_generated.deepcopy.go && echo \"DeepCopy methods generated\" || echo \"Generation failed\"\n276: ```\n277: \n278: **Acceptance Criteria**:\n279: - `zz_generated.deepcopy.go` file exists\n280: - Contains `DeepCopy()` methods for all types\n281: - Contains `DeepCopyInto()` methods for all types\n282: - Contains `DeepCopyObject()` methods implementing `runtime.Object`\n283: - No compilation errors in generated code\n284: \n285: ---\n286: \n287: ### [ ] TASK-013: Test DeepCopy methods\n288: **Description**: Write and run tests to verify DeepCopy methods work correctly.\n289: \n290: **Test File**: `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime_types_test.go`\n291: \n292: **Test Cases**:\n293: - Test `DeepCopy()` creates independent copies\n294: - Test modifications to copy don't affect original\n295: - Test nested structs are deep copied\n296: - Test slice fields are deep copied\n297: \n298: **Verification**:\n299: ```bash\n300: go test ./pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/ -run TestDeepCopy -v\n301: ```\n302: \n303: **Acceptance Criteria**:\n304: - All DeepCopy tests pass\n305: - Copies are independent from originals\n306: - No shared references between original and copy\n307: \n308: ---\n309: \n310: ### [ ] TASK-014: Generate CRD YAML manifests\n311: **Description**: Run controller-gen to generate CRD YAML files.\n312: \n313: **Command**:\n314: ```bash\n315: controller-gen crd paths=\"./pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/...\" output:crd:dir=manifests/charts/base/crds\n316: ```\n317: \n318: **Verification**:\n319: ```bash\n320: test -f manifests/charts/base/crds/runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh_agentruntimes.yaml && echo \"CRD generated\" || echo \"Generation failed\"\n321: ```\n322: \n323: **Acceptance Criteria**:\n324: - CRD file exists at expected location\n325: - API group is `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`\n326: - Kind is `AgentRuntime`\n327: - ShortNames include `art`\n328: - Scope is `Namespaced`\n329: - OpenAPI v3 schema is complete\n330: - Default values are configured\n331: - Validation rules are present\n332: \n333: ---\n334: \n335: ### [ ] TASK-015: Validate CRD YAML with dry-run\n336: **Description**: Apply CRD with dry-run to validate schema and structure.\n337: \n338: **Command**:\n339: ```bash\n340: kubectl apply --dry-run=client -f manifests/charts/base/crds/runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh_agentruntimes.yaml\n341: ```\n342: \n343: **Verification**:\n344: ```bash\n345: kubectl apply --dry-run=client -f manifests/charts/base/crds/runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh_agentruntimes.yaml\n346: ```\n347: \n348: **Acceptance Criteria**:\n349: - kubectl dry-run succeeds without errors\n350: - CRD schema is valid\n351: - No validation errors in the manifest\n352: \n353: ---\n354: \n355: ### [ ] TASK-016: Generate client-go code\n356: **Description**: Run code-generator to produce typed clients, informers, and listers.\n357: \n358: **Command**:\n359: ```bash\n360: bash hack/update-codegen.sh\n361: ```\n362: \n363: **Verification**:\n364: ```bash\n365: test -f client-go/clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime.go && echo \"Client generated\" || echo \"Generation failed\"\n366: ```\n367: \n368: **Acceptance Criteria**:\n369: - `agentruntime.go` exists with `AgentRuntimeInterface`\n370: - `AgentRuntimeList` types are generated\n371: - Informer factory includes AgentRuntime support\n372: - Lister includes AgentRuntime support\n373: - All generated code compiles without errors\n374: \n375: ---\n376: \n377: ### [ ] TASK-017: Test client-go operations\n378: **Description**: Write tests to verify generated client-go works correctly.\n379: \n380: **Test File**: `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/client_test.go`\n381: \n382: **Test Cases**:\n383: - Test `AgentRuntimeInterface` methods exist\n384: - Test client can be instantiated\n385: - Test resource types are correct\n386: - Test fake client works for testing\n387: \n388: **Verification**:\n389: ```bash\n390: go test ./pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/ -run TestClientGo -v\n391: ```\n392: \n393: **Acceptance Criteria**:\n394: - Client interface tests pass\n395: - Fake client can be instantiated\n396: - Resource types match expectations\n397: \n398: ---\n399: \n400: ## Phase 4: Validation and Testing\n401: ### [ ] TASK-018: Write unit tests for type validation\n402: **Description**: Create comprehensive unit tests for type definitions and validation.\n403: \n404: **Test File**: `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime_types_test.go`\n405: \n406: **Test Coverage**:\n407: - Required field validation\n408: - Default value application\n409: - Enum validation for protocol\n410: - Port range validation\n411: - JSON serialization/deserialization\n412: - YAML serialization/deserialization\n413: \n414: **Verification**:\n415: ```bash\n416: go test ./pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/ -cover\n417: ```\n418: \n419: **Acceptance Criteria**:\n420: - All validation tests pass\n421: - Code coverage > 80% for type definitions\n422: - Edge cases are covered\n423: \n424: ---\n425: \n426: ### [ ] TASK-019: Test default values\n427: **Description**: Verify that kubebuilder default values are applied correctly.\n428: \n429: **Test File**: `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/defaults_test.go`\n430: \n431: **Test Cases**:\n432: - `SessionTimeout` defaults to \"15m\"\n433: - `MaxSessionDuration` defaults to \"8h\"\n434: - Explicit values override defaults\n435: - Defaults are applied during creation\n436: \n437: **Verification**:\n438: ```bash\n439: go test ./pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/ -run TestDefaults -v\n440: ```\n441: \n442: **Acceptance Criteria**:\n443: - All default value tests pass\n444: - Defaulting webhook (if used) applies defaults correctly\n445: \n446: ---\n447: \n448: ### [ ] TASK-020: Test OpenAPI validation rules\n449: **Description**: Verify that OpenAPI validation rules enforce constraints correctly.\n450: \n451: **Test File**: `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/validation_test.go`\n452: \n453: **Test Cases**:\n454: - Missing required fields are rejected\n455: - Invalid enum values are rejected\n456: - Port numbers outside range are rejected\n457: - Empty targetPort array is rejected\n458: - Invalid duration formats are rejected\n459: \n460: **Verification**:\n461: ```bash\n462: go test ./pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/ -run TestValidation -v\n463: ```\n464: \n465: **Acceptance Criteria**:\n466: - All validation tests pass\n467: - Invalid requests are properly rejected\n468: - Error messages are clear and helpful\n469: \n470: ---\n471: \n472: ### [ ] TASK-021: Create integration test with envtest\n473: **Description**: Create integration tests using controller-runtime envtest.\n474: \n475: **Test File**: `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/integration_test.go`\n476: \n477: **Test Cases**:\n478: - Create AgentRuntime via API server\n479: - Get AgentRuntime from API server\n480: - Update AgentRuntime spec\n481: - Update AgentRuntime status (subresource)\n482: - List AgentRuntime resources\n483: - Watch AgentRuntime resources\n484: - Delete AgentRuntime resources\n485: \n486: **Verification**:\n487: ```bash\n488: go test ./pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/ -run TestIntegration -v\n489: ```\n490: \n491: **Acceptance Criteria**:\n492: - All integration tests pass\n493: - CRUD operations work correctly\n494: - Status subresource updates work independently\n495: - Watch events are received correctly\n496: \n497: ---\n498: \n499: ### [ ] TASK-022: Test print columns configuration\n500: **Description**: Verify that kubectl print columns are configured correctly.\n501: \n502: **Test File**: `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/printcolumns_test.go`\n503: \n504: **Test Cases**:\n505: - Age column displays correctly\n506: - Additional print columns (if any) work\n507: - Column types are correct\n508: - JSONPath expressions resolve correctly\n509: \n510: **Verification**:\n511: ```bash\n512: go test ./pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/ -run TestPrintColumns -v\n513: ```\n514: \n515: **Acceptance Criteria**:\n516: - Print column tests pass\n517: - Age column shows correct duration\n518: - Columns are properly formatted\n519: \n520: ---\n521: \n522: ### [ ] TASK-023: Run all tests\n523: **Description**: Run complete test suite to verify all functionality.\n524: \n525: **Command**:\n526: ```bash\n527: go test ./pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/... -v -race -cover\n528: ```\n529: \n530: **Verification**:\n531: ```bash\n532: go test ./pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/... -v -race -cover\n533: ```\n534: \n535: **Acceptance Criteria**:\n536: - All tests pass\n537: - No race conditions detected\n538: - Overall code coverage > 80%\n539: \n540: ---\n541: \n542: ## Phase 5: Documentation and Examples\n543: ### [ ] TASK-024: Create example AgentRuntime YAML\n544: **Description**: Create example YAML manifest demonstrating AgentRuntime usage.\n545: \n546: **File**: `examples/agentruntime.yaml`\n547: \n548: **Requirements**:\n549: - Complete example with all fields\n550: - Shows default value behavior\n551: - Shows valid targetPort configuration\n552: - Shows podTemplate with container\n553: - Includes comments explaining each field\n554: \n555: **Verification**:\n556: ```bash\n557: kubectl apply --dry-run=client -f examples/agentruntime.yaml\n558: ```\n559: \n560: **Acceptance Criteria**:\n561: - YAML is syntactically valid\n562: - Example can be applied with dry-run\n563: - All fields are documented in comments\n564: \n565: ---\n566: \n567: ### [ ] TASK-025: Update documentation\n568: **Description**: Update relevant documentation to reflect the implementation.\n569: \n570: **Files to Update**:\n571: - `README.md` (if applicable)\n572: - `deployment/design.md` (update implementation status)\n573: - `changes/AR-001/README.md` (mark tasks complete)\n574: \n575: **Requirements**:\n576: - Document API group and version\n577: - Document available fields and their purposes\n578: - Document default values\n579: - Document validation rules\n580: - Document usage examples\n581: \n582: **Verification**:\n583: ```bash\n584: grep -q \"AgentRuntime\" README.md || echo \"Documentation missing\"\n585: ```\n586: \n587: **Acceptance Criteria**:\n588: - Documentation is updated\n589: - Examples are provided\n590: - API usage is clearly documented\n591: \n592: ---\n593: \n594: ## Phase 6: Code Quality and Finalization\n595: ### [ ] TASK-026: Run linters\n596: **Description**: Run Go linters to ensure code quality.\n597: \n598: **Commands**:\n599: ```bash\n600: gofmt -s -w pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/\n601: go vet ./pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/...\n602: golangci-lint run pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/...\n603: ```\n604: \n605: **Verification**:\n606: ```bash\n607: gofmt -l pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/\n608: go vet ./pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/...\n609: ```\n610: \n611: **Acceptance Criteria**:\n612: - Code is properly formatted\n613: - No vet warnings\n614: - No linter errors\n615: \n616: ---\n617: \n618: ### [ ] TASK-027: Verify generated code is up-to-date\n619: **Description**: Ensure generated code matches current source definitions.\n620: \n621: **Commands**:\n622: ```bash\n623: make generate\n624: make gen-client\n625: ```\n626: \n627: **Verification**:\n628: ```bash\n629: git diff pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/zz_generated.deepcopy.go\n630: git diff client-go/\n631: ```\n632: \n633: **Acceptance Criteria**:\n634: - No uncommitted changes in generated files\n635: - Generated code is current\n636: - All make targets succeed\n637: \n638: ---\n639: \n640: ### [ ] TASK-028: Create Makefile targets (if missing)\n641: **Description**: Ensure Makefile has targets